@@$TJvCaptionPanel
<TITLE TJvCaptionPanel overview>
<GROUP JVCL.Miscel>
  TJvCaptionPanel is a panel with a caption bar so it looks like a form. The caption panel will
  contain the caption of the panel along with 0 or more caption buttons.

  To use a panel with a caption in your form:

  * Drop a TJvCaptionPanel on the form or any control that accepts child controls.
  * Set the <LINK TJvCaptionPanel.Caption, caption> of the panel.
  * Specify the <LINK TJvCaptionPanel.Buttons, caption buttons> the panel should have.
  * Specify the <LINK TJvCaptionPanel.CaptionColor, color> of the caption bar.
  * Specify the <LINK TJvCaptionPanel.CaptionFont, font> of the caption bar.
  * Specify the <LINK TJvCaptionPanel.CaptionPosition, position> of the caption bar.
  * Specify if <LINK TJvCaptionPanel.FlatButtons, flat buttons> are needed.
  * Assign a <LINK TJvCaptionPanel.OnButtonClick, OnButtonClick event handler> to take action when
    a caption button is clicked.
